    <section class="content">
        <h1>Solutions for Educational Data Privacy</h1>
        
        <h2>For Students</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Use strong, unique passwords for educational accounts</li>
            <li>Enable 2FA on all educational platforms</li>
            <li>Be cautious about sharing personal information in online learning environments</li>
            <li>Regularly review privacy settings on educational apps</li>
            <li>Understand your rights regarding educational records</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>For Educational Institutions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Implement transparent data practices for students and parents</li>
            <li>Create privacy-first educational technology policies</li>
            <li>Prioritize student privacy over data collection</li>
            <li>View students as partners in privacy protection</li>
            <li>Conduct regular privacy impact assessments for educational systems</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Technical Measures for Educational Data</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Encryption of student data both in transit and at rest</li>
            <li>Strict access controls for educational records</li>
            <li>Regular security audits of educational technology systems</li>
            <li>Secure email practices for communicating student information</li>
            <li>Data minimization in educational analytics</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Policy Recommendations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Clear data retention policies for student records</li>
            <li>Transparent data sharing agreements with educational technology vendors</li>
            <li>Regular privacy training for educational staff</li>
            <li>Student and parental consent processes for data processing</li>
            <li>Incident response plans for educational data breaches</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>GDPR Implementation in Educational Context</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Appoint Data Protection Officers in educational institutions</li>
            <li>Conduct Data Protection Impact Assessments for educational processing</li>
            <li>Implement age-appropriate consent mechanisms</li>
            <li>Ensure lawful basis for processing student data</li>
            <li>Facilitate student data rights exercises</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
